      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>Il cannone elettronico, la lamina di materiale cristallino e lo schermo ai fosfori sono montati all’interno di un’ampolla di vetro sotto vuoto.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame11" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="1.5189in" svg:y="1.1098in" svg:width="0.7in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="291">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Fig. 5</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame12" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="3.7165in" svg:y="1.1098in" svg:width="0.7in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="292">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Fig. 6</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame13" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="5.6189in" svg:y="1.1098in" svg:width="0.7in" svg:height="0.5in" draw:z-index="293">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Fig. 7</text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>La figura 5 mostra una foto di quest’ampolla, mentre le figure 6 e 7 mostrano in dettaglio il cannone elettronico.</text:p>
