    </draw:frame><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Frame27" text:anchor-type="char" svg:x="1.4689in" svg:y="1.3374in" svg:width="0.4in" svg:height="0.3in" draw:z-index="317">
     <draw:text-box>
      <text:p text:style-name="Standard"><text:span text:style-name="T5"></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T6">2</text:span></text:p>
     </draw:text-box>
    </draw:frame>La figura 13 riporta due grafici delle misure effettuate, uno con la tensione <text:span text:style-name="T8">V</text:span> in ordinata, l’altro con l’inverso della radice della tensione <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr15" draw:name="Object15" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.3902in" svg:height="0.211in" draw:z-index="3"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <msup>
           <mi>V</mi>
           <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
            <mrow>
             <mrow>
              <mo stretchy="false">−</mo>
              <mn>1</mn>
             </mrow>
             <mo stretchy="false">/</mo>
             <mn>2</mn>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
          </msup>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{V rSup { size 8{ -  {1} slash {2} } } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
