   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Per definizione se una matrice è uguale alla sua aggiunta <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr15" draw:name="Object83" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.4902in" svg:height="0.211in" draw:z-index="71"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mi>A</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
           <msup>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mrow>
              <mo stretchy="false">+</mo>
              <mrow/>
             </mrow>
            </mstyle>
           </msup>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{A=A rSup { size 8{+{}} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD1QAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIAAiAFEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       tP///+AEAAC0AQAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAAAgABAAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEAAAAC
       BAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAIAAAAMgr3AF8EAQAAACsAEAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAA
       AAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAACAAAADIKwAHCAQEAAAA9ABUAAAD7AkD+
       AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQAABAAAAPABAQAIAAAA
       MgrAAT0DAQAAAEEACAAAADIKwAFcAAEAAABBAAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsC
       FAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIiU3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAAAwAAAAAA
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, allora si dice che è hermitiana, se invece la matrice è uguale alla sua aggiunta cambiata di segno <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr15" draw:name="Object84" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.6181in" svg:height="0.211in" draw:z-index="72"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mi>A</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
           <mrow>
            <mo stretchy="false">−</mo>
            <msup>
             <mi>A</mi>
             <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
              <mrow>
               <mo stretchy="false">+</mo>
               <mrow/>
              </mrow>
             </mstyle>
            </msup>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{A= - A rSup { size 8{+{}} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD3QAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIAAiAGEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       tP///+AFAAC0AQAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAAAgABAAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEAAAAC
       BAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAIAAAAMgr3AGIFAQAAACsAEAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAA
       AAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAACAAAADIKwAEaAwEAAAAtAAgAAAAyCsAB
       wgEBAAAAPQAVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1lcyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAH4EAAAA
       LQEAAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIKwAFABAEAAABBAAgAAAAyCsABXAABAAAAQQAKAAAAJgYPAAoA
       /////wEAAAAAABAAAAD7AhQACQAAAAAAvAIAAAAAAQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAQAEAAAA
       8AEAAAMAAAAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, allora si dice che è antihermitiana. Una matrice tale che <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr15" draw:name="Object85" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="1.0327in" svg:height="0.211in" draw:z-index="73"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mstyle mathvariant="italic">
             <msup>
              <mtext>AA</mtext>
              <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
               <mrow>
                <mo stretchy="false">+</mo>
                <mrow/>
               </mrow>
              </mstyle>
             </msup>
            </mstyle>
            <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
            <msup>
             <mi>A</mi>
             <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
              <mrow>
               <mo stretchy="false">+</mo>
               <mrow/>
              </mrow>
             </mstyle>
            </msup>
           </mrow>
           <mrow>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
            <mi>I</mi>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital &quot;AA&quot; rSup { size 8{+{}} } =A rSup { size 8{+{}} } A=I} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD9QAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIAAuAKEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       tP///6AKAAC0AQAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAAAgABUAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAA
       BAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQAACAAAADIKwAHTCQEAAABJAAgAAAAyCsAB
       BwcBAAAAQQAIAAAAMgrAASIFAQAAAEEACAAAADIKwAFcAAIAAABBQRAAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAA
       kAEAAAACBAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAQAEAAAA8AEAAAgAAAAyCsABbQgBAAAAPQAIAAAA
       MgrAAacDAQAAAD0AEAAAAPsCIP8AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEAAAQA
       AADwAQEACAAAADIK9wBEBgEAAAArAAgAAAAyCvcAjwIBAAAAKwAKAAAAJgYPAAoA/////wEA
       AAAAABAAAAD7AhQACQAAAAAAvAIAAAAAAQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAQAEAAAA8AEAAAMA
       AAAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, dove <text:span text:style-name="T8">I</text:span> è la matrice identità, si dice che è unitaria.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">L’operazione di prendere la matrice aggiunta nel campo dellle matrici assume il ruolo dell’operazione di prendere il complesso coniugato nel campo dei numeri complessi. Quindi le matrici hermitiane assumono il ruolo dei numeri reali puri, mentre le matrici antihermitiane assumono il ruolo dei numeri immaginari puri. Le matrici unitarie, infine, assumono il ruolo dei numeri a modulo unitario.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Le matrici hermitiane, le antihermitiane e le unitarie hanno delle proprietà molto interessanti che studieremo più avanti, ed hanno una notevole importanza in Meccanica Quantistica.</text:p>
   <text:list text:style-name="WW8Num2">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:h text:style-name="P22" text:outline-level="3">Rapporto tra matrici ed operatori.</text:h>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Nel caso di vettori a dimensione finita sappiamo, dagli studi di algebra lineare, che un qualunque operatore lineare <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr15" draw:name="Object86" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.6083in" svg:height="0.1945in" draw:z-index="74"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
           <mi>v</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo>
           <mover accent="true">
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>R</mi>
            </mstyle>
            <mo stretchy="true">⃗</mo>
           </mover>
           <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
           <mi>w</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ \lline v \rangle  widevec  { size 8{R} }  \lline w \rangle } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADMwEAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADALgAiAJEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       wP///+AIAACgAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABwAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
       AAAtAQAABQAAABQCiQBIAAUAAAATApcCSAAFAAAAFAKJAHoBBQAAABMCkAHbAQUAAAAUApAB
       2wEFAAAAEwKXAnoBBQAAABQCiQDQBgUAAAATApcC0AYFAAAAFAKJAGQIBQAAABMCkAHFCAUA
       AAAUApABxQgFAAAAEwKXAmQIFQAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQEAAAAEAgAQVGltZXMgTmV3IFJv
       bWFuAACDBAAAAC0BAQAIAAAAMgoAAigHAQAAAHcACAAAADIKAAKSAAEAAAB2ABUAAAD7AoD+
       AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQIABAAAAPABAQAIAAAA
       MgpCAfkDAQAAAFIAEAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEBAAQA
       AADwAQIACAAAADIKAAJrAwEAAAC+AAgAAAAyCgACAQUBAAAArgAIAAAAMgoAAkACAQAAAL4A
       CgAAACYGDwAKAP////8BAAAAAAAQAAAA+wIUAAkAAAAAALwCAAAAAAECAiJTeXN0ZW0AAAQA
       AAAtAQIABAAAAPABAQADAAAAAAA=
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>può essere scritto come un prodotto matriciale <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr15" draw:name="Object87" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.7717in" svg:height="0.1945in" draw:z-index="75"><draw:object>
